touchpad-indicator is a minimalist Touchpad management extension for the Gnome Shell.

touchpad-indicator allows you to switch your Touchpad On or Off, if a Trackpoint exists it is also possible to switch it On or Off.

It is possible to automatically switch off the touchpad at startup of gnome-shell, if a mouse is detected. 
Default is that the automatc switch off is disabled.

To choose your preferred option you could change the values below "General Settings".


To install, extract the archive or copy the folder to
~/.local/share/gnome-shell/extensions/ and restart the shell.
